  "description": "Dividing an IP address space into smaller networks using subnet masks.",
  "fullExplanation": "CIDR (Classless Inter-Domain Routing) replaced classful networking in 1993. A prefix like 192.168.1.0/24 means the first 24 bits identify the network, the remaining 8 bits identify hosts. Subnetting borrows bits from the host portion to create more networks with fewer hosts each. VLSM (Variable Length Subnet Masking) allows different subnet sizes within the same network.",
